To turn this mock-up into a colorful and interactive website, you'll need to create a simple HTML structure with CSS classes to style the elements. Additionally, you'll need to create a JavaScript function to replace the joke with a real joke based on user input. Here's a sample code:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Joke Website</title>
    <style>
        .text {
            text-align: center;
            margin: 0;
            width: 100%;
        }
        .joke-button {
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 15%;
            left: 0;
            margin: 5%;
            background-color: blue;
            padding: 8%;
            border-radius: 5%;
        }
        .reveal-button {
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 18%;
            left: 0;
            margin: 5%;
            background-color: blue;
            padding: 8%;
            border-radius: 5%;
        }
        .button-box {
            display: flex;
        }
        .joke-pun {
            align-items: center;
            display: flex;
            width: 100%;
            align-content: flex-start;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div>
        <button class="joke-button">Push To Reveal Punchline</button>
        <button class="reveal-button">Reveal Punchline?</button>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
        <p id="punchline"></p>
    </div>
    <script>
        const revealButton = document.querySelector('.reveal-button');
        const punchlineDiv = document.querySelector('#punchline');

        function replaceJoke() {
            revealButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
                if (punchlineDiv.textContent === 'Reveal Punchline?') {
                    const joke = 'Why couldn't the bicycle stand up by itself?';
                    punchlineDiv.textContent = joke;
                    revealButton.textContent = 'Hide Punchline';
                }
            });
        }

        replaceJoke();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```
This code creates a simple website with a "Push To Reveal Punchline" button and a "Reveal Punchline?" button below it. The JavaScript replaces the joke when the "Push To Reveal Punchline" button is clicked.
